TITLE: Creating an Order with PayPal API in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a new PayPal order using the OrdersController. This method allows merchants to add Level 2 and 3 data to payments to reduce risk and processing costs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paypal/paypal-typescript-server-sdk/blob/main/doc/controllers/orders.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async createOrder(
  body: OrderRequest,
  paypalMockResponse?: string,
  paypalRequestId?: string,
  paypalPartnerAttributionId?: string,
  paypalClientMetadataId?: string,
  prefer?: string,
  paypalAuthAssertion?: string,
  requestOptions?: RequestOptions
): Promise<ApiResponse<Order>>
```

