TITLE: Defining AVS Code Enumeration in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript enumeration defining all possible address verification response codes used in payment processing. Includes codes for address matches, ZIP code matches, international transactions, and service availability states across major card networks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paypal/paypal-typescript-server-sdk/blob/main/doc/models/avs-code.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
enum AvsCode {
  AvsA,  // Address matches, ZIP code doesn't (Visa/MC/Discover) or address correct (Amex)
  AvsB,  // Address matches, International A
  AvsC,  // No matches, International N
  AvsD,  // Address and postal code match, International X
  AvsE,  // Not allowed for Internet/phone or incorrect name but address/postal match (Amex)
  AvsF,  // Address and postal match (UK specific X) or incorrect name but address matches (Amex)
  AvsG,  // Global unavailable, nothing matches
  AvsI,  // International unavailable
  AvsM,  // Address and postal match or name/address/postal match (Amex)
  AvsN,  // Nothing matches or address/postal incorrect (Amex)
  AvsP,  // Postal international Z, postal code only
  AvsR,  // Retry request or system unavailable (Amex)
  AvsS,  // Service not supported
  AvsU,  // Service unavailable or information unavailable
  AvsW,  // Whole ZIP code or all incorrect (Amex)
  AvsX,  // Exact match of address and nine-digit ZIP
  AvsY,  // Address and five-digit ZIP match
  AvsZ,  // Five-digit ZIP matches, no address
  AvsNull,  // No AVS response obtained (Maestro)
  Avs0,  // All address information matches (Maestro)
  Avs1,  // No address information matches (Maestro)
  Avs2,  // Partial address information matches (Maestro)
  Avs3,  // Address information not processed (Maestro)
  Avs4   // Address check unavailable (Maestro)
}
```

