TITLE: Payment Advice Code Enumeration Definition in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Enumeration of payment advice codes returned by card networks (Visa and Mastercard) for declined transactions. Each code represents a specific scenario and provides guidance on how to handle the declined payment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paypal/paypal-typescript-server-sdk/blob/main/doc/models/payment-advice-code.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
enum PaymentAdviceCode {
  PaymentAdvice01, // Mastercard: expired card account upgrade
  PaymentAdvice02, // Mastercard: over credit limit, Visa: stop specific payment
  PaymentAdvice03, // Mastercard: fraudulent account, Visa: stop all recurring payments
  PaymentAdvice04, // Mastercard: token requirements not fulfilled
  PaymentAdvice21, // Mastercard/Visa: cancel recurring payments
  PaymentAdvice22, // Mastercard: merchant qualification issue
  PaymentAdvice24, // Mastercard: retry after 1 hour
  PaymentAdvice25, // Mastercard: retry after 24 hours
  PaymentAdvice26, // Mastercard: retry after 2 days
  PaymentAdvice27, // Mastercard: retry after 4 days
  PaymentAdvice28, // Mastercard: retry after 6 days
  PaymentAdvice29, // Mastercard: retry after 8 days
  PaymentAdvice30, // Mastercard: retry after 10 days
  PaymentAdvice40, // Mastercard: consumer non-reloadable prepaid card
  PaymentAdvice43  // Mastercard: consumer multi-use virtual card number
}
```

