TITLE: Adding OAuth Token Update Callback in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to add a callback function that will be executed whenever the OAuth token is updated. It can be used to perform operations like saving the token to a database or file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paypal/paypal-typescript-server-sdk/blob/main/doc/auth/oauth-2-client-credentials-grant.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const client = new Client({
  clientCredentialsAuthCredentials: {
    oAuthClientId: 'OAuthClientId',
    oAuthClientSecret: 'OAuthClientSecret',
    oAuthOnTokenUpdate: (token: OAuthToken) => {
      // Add the callback handler to perform operations like save to DB or file etc.
      // It will be triggered whenever the token gets updated
      saveTokenToDatabase(token);
    }
  },
});
```

